text:
West street, Beach Street, to Hubert Street, (Before reconstruction).
June 9, 1918.

234 to 230 West Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of Beach Street, showing four 4-story buildings. On the left appear structures on the north side of Beach Street, east from West to Washington Streets. The 75 foot piles shown are for foundation work for the southward extension of the West Side Express Highway.

July 28, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

West Street, north from Beach Street, showing on the left. (west side of street) piers No. 27-28 and 29 North River, the Pennsylvania Railroad Produce Terminal.

August 2, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
